{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772382951,"nonce":"CvQNQe6yA+C3XXNIGGtecLOAf04=","title":"Password change does not require current password","message":"UsersController#update allows changing the password without verifying the current password. The form only has 'new password' and 'confirm password' fields -- no 'current password' field.\n\nImpact:\n- Session hijacking: brief access to a logged-in session allows permanent account takeover\n- CSRF risk: forged form submission could change a user's password\n- Violates security best practices\n\nFix: add a current_password field to the form and validate it before allowing password changes. Devise has built-in support for this via update_with_password.\n\nFiles involved:\n- app/controllers/users_controller.rb (user_params, update action)\n- app/views/users/_form.html.erb (password section)\n- app/models/user.rb\n\nPriority: P0 -- must fix before user testing.","files":null}]}